sident-visa.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>fill out forms,<\/strong><\/a> gather the required documents, and complete a <strong>medical examination<\/strong>. However, the specific requirements vary based on the type of visitor visa the parents are applying for.<\/p>\n<p>Applying for a visitor visa can be a complex and time-consuming process, but with the right guidance and information, you can easily navigate through it. In this guide, we will discuss the eligibility requirements and application process to follow when applying for a visitor visa Canada for parents.[\/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221; content_placement=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221;][vc_column_inner column_padding=&#8221;padding-6-percent&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; centered_text=&#8221;true&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221;][nectar_btn size=&#8221;large&#8221; button_style=&#8221;regular&#8221; button_color_2=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; icon_family=&#8221;default_arrow&#8221; text=&#8221;Apply for Parents Tourist Visa&#8221; url=&#8221;https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/contact-us\/&#8221;][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_column_text]\n<h2 id=\"definition\">Understanding Visitor Visa for Canada<\/h2>\n<p>Before you start the application process, it is important to understand what a visitor visa is and what it entails. A visitor visa is a legal document that allows individuals to enter Canada for a limited period of time. It is issued by the Canadian government and is necessary for anyone who is not a Canadian citizen or permanent resident to enter Canada. A visitor visa is also known as a temporary resident visa (TRV) and is usually issued for a period of up to six months.[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\n<h2 id=\"eligibility\">Eligibility for Canada Visitor Visa for Parents<\/h2>\n<p>Before you apply for a visitor visa for your parents, it is important to determine their eligibility. To be eligible for a visitor visa, your parents must meet the following requirements:<\/p>\n<h3>Age Requirements<\/h3>\n<p>The age requirements for a Canada Visitor Visa for Parents depend on the type of visa being applied for. Generally, there is <strong>no minimum age requirement<\/strong>, but elderly parents may need to provide additional <strong>medical documentation<\/strong> to prove their ability to travel and remain healthy during their stay in Canada. However, any dependents accompanying them to Canada must be under 22 and unmarried.<\/p>\n<h3>Health Requirements<\/h3>\n<p>Visitor visa Canada applicants must pass a medical examination from an approved medical officer. They must also provide medical test results or reports for any pre-existing medical conditions.<\/p>\n<p>Applicants who are applying for a parent <a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/family-sponsorship\/super-visa-parents-grandparents\/\"><strong>Super Visa<\/strong> <\/a>must demonstrate that they have medical insurance coverage from a Canadian provider. This coverage should be valid for at least one year from the date they intend to enter Canada and offer a minimum of <strong>$100,000<\/strong> in emergency medical coverage.<\/p>\n<h3>Financial Requirements<\/h3>\n<p>Your parents must be able to support themselves financially during their stay in Canada. This can include bank statements, proof of employment, and other financial documents. There is no strict finance amount requirement, but each individual should have at least <strong>$1,230<\/strong> for each month they intend to stay in the country.<\/p>\n<p>Parents can bypass this requirement by having their Canadian child write a letter promising to financially support them during their stay in Canada.<\/p>\n<h3>Criminal History<\/h3>\n<p>Neither parent should have a criminal history. If one of them was convicted of a crime in the past, they would need to write an explanation letter detailing that their conviction was overturned and that they are no longer inadmissible to Canada.<\/p>\n<h3>Purpose of Visit<\/h3>\n<p>The parents will need to describe a specific reason why they are visiting Canada. In most cases, they can state that they are simply visiting their child or children who reside in the country. If they intend to visit Canada for a specific event, such as a wedding, they should state so.<\/p>\n<p>Visa officers may reject parents who can\u2019t provide a convincing explanation, so it is important to provide clear details of the intended visit.<\/p>\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"qVdP0TISYT\"><p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/blog\/a-perfect-purpose-of-travel-for-canada-visitor-visa-sample-letter\/\">A Perfect Purpose of Travel for Canada Visitor Visa (Sample Letter)<\/a><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"&#8220;A Perfect Purpose of Travel for Canada Visitor Visa (Sample Letter)&#8221; &#8212; Colossus Migration\" src=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/blog\/a-perfect-purpose-of-travel-for-canada-visitor-visa-sample-letter\/embed\/#?secret=r77ZmHCViq#?secret=qVdP0TISYT\" data-secret=\"qVdP0TISYT\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"><\/iframe><\/p>\n<h3>Intent to Leave Canada<\/h3>\n<p>Your parents must prove that they have ties to their home country and that they plan to return after their visit to Canada. This can include a job, a home, or family ties in their home country.[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\n<h2 id=\"types\">Different Types of Visitor Visa Available<\/h2>\n<p>The following types of visitor visas are available:<\/p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><b>Visitor Visa Name<\/b><\/td>\n<td><b>Issued To<\/b><\/td>\n<td><b>Single Entry or Multiple Entry<\/b><\/td>\n<td><b>Validity Period<\/b><\/td>\n<td><b>Restrictions<\/b><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Single-Entry Visa<\/span><\/td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Anyone<\/span><\/td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Single Entry<\/span><\/td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">6 months<\/span><\/td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must not stay in Canada for more than 6 months at a time<\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Multiple-Entry Visa<\/span><\/td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Anyone<\/span><\/td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Multiple Entry<\/span><\/td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Up to 10 years<\/span><\/td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must not stay in Canada for more than 6 months at a time<\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Super Visa<\/span><\/td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Parents and Grandparent<\/span><\/td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Multiple Entry<\/span><\/td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Up to 10 years<\/span><\/td>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Must not stay in Canada for more than 5 years at a time<\/span><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Business Visitor Vi