ths beyond their intended stay in Canada.<\/p>\n<h3>Application Form<\/h3>\n<p>Your parents must fill out an application form for a visitor visa. The form can be downloaded from the Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC) website.<\/p>\n<h3>Photographs<\/h3>\n<p>Your parents will need to provide two passport-sized photographs that meet the IRCC requirements.<\/p>\n<h3>Proof of Financial Support<\/h3>\n<p>Your parents must provide proof that they have enough money to support themselves during their stay in Canada. This can include bank statements, proof of employment, and other financial documents.<\/p>\n<h3>Travel Itinerary<\/h3>\n<p>Your parents will need to provide a detailed travel itinerary, including information on their flights, accommodations, and activities while in Canada.<\/p>\n<h3>Invitation Letter<\/h3>\n<p>You will need to provide an invitation letter for your parents, stating the purpose of their visit, the length of their stay, and your relationship with them.<\/p>\n<h3>Other Documents<\/h3>\n<p>Additional documents may be required depending on your parents&#8217; specific circumstances. This can include medical certificates, police certificates, and other documents.[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\n<h2 id=\"tips\">Tips to Ensure the Visitor Visa Application Documents are Complete<\/h2>\n<p>Parents who intend to apply for a visitor visa application must ensure they provide all the documents required. Some ways to make this process easier include:<\/p>\n<h3>Starting Early<\/h3>\n<p>Many of the required documents take several days, if not weeks to acquire. For this reason, visitor visa applicants should start gathering them many weeks in advance.<\/p>\n<h3>Reading the Instructions Carefully<\/h3>\n<p>Visitor visa applicants should read the instructions in the visitor visa application guide carefully to understand the application process, requirements, and special considerations.<\/p>\n<h3>Double-Checking Information<\/h3>\n<p>It is vital to double-check all the information mentioned in the forms. This reduces the chances of making a mistake that could get the application rejected.<\/p>\n<h3>Submitting All the Required Documents<\/h3>\n<p>Visitor visa applicants should review the visitor visa document checklist and ensure they submit each of the required documents.<\/p>\n<h3>Seeking Professional Help<\/h3>\n<p>Parents should seek professional help from a Regulated Canadian Immigration Consultant to optimize their application and eliminate any mistakes. This will improve the chances of their application being approved.[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\n<h2 id=\"application\">Visitor Visa Application Process<\/h2>\n<p>Visitor visa Canada applicants must follow the steps described below to apply for their visa:<\/p>\n<h3>Determining Eligibility<\/h3>\n<p>Before you apply for a visitor visa for your parents, it is important to determine their eligibility. To be eligible for a visitor visa, your parents must meet the requirements mentioned in the previous section.<\/p>\n<h3>Gathering the Supporting Documents<\/h3>\n<p>Once your parents have determined their eligibility for a visitor visa, they will need to gather the required documents listed in their document checklist.<\/p>\n<h3>Completing the Application Form<\/h3>\n<p>Next, your parents must fill out an application form for a visitor visa. The form can be downloaded from the Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC) website.<\/p>\n<h3>Paying the Application Fees<\/h3>\n<p>The visitor visa applicant must then pay the application fees before submitting their application. This fee amount is <strong>$100<\/strong> per person for all kinds of visitor visas. This includes single entry, multiple entry, and Super Visas. Applicants can pay this fee online or at a visa processing center.<\/p>\n<h3>Submit the Application<\/h3>\n<p>Once all the required documents are gathered, your parents can submit their visitor visa application. The application can be submitted online or in person at a Visa Application Centre (VAC) or a Canadian embassy or consulate. The application fee must be paid at the time of submission.<\/p>\n<h3>Receiving the Decision<\/h3>\n<p>Once the visitor visa applicant has submitted their application, they must wait for Immigration, Refugees, and Citizenship Canada (IRCC) to review it and reach a decision. If approved, they will be issued a visitor visa and can enter Canada.<\/p>\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"ED0W1ay4Tk\"><p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/blog\/convert-visitor-visa-to-work-permit-canada\/\">Visitor Visa to Work Permit Canada: The Ultimate Guide<\/a><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"&#8220;Visitor Visa to Work Permit Canada: The Ultimate Guide&#8221; &#8212; Colossus Migration\" src=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/blog\/convert-visitor-visa-to-work-permit-canada\/embed\/#?secret=OAyCP9IPsV#?secret=ED0W1ay4Tk\" data-secret=\"ED0W1ay4Tk\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"><\/iframe><\/p>\n<h2 id=\"processing\">Processing Times for Canada Visitor Visa for Parents<\/h2>\n<p>The visitor visa processing time typically varies depending on the country the applicant is applying from. For example, the processing time for applicants from India is approximately <strong>17 days<\/strong>. This processing time could be longer if IRCC is experiencing a large volume of applications or if they have requested additional documents from the applicant.<\/p>\n<p>It is possible to apply for <strong>urgent visa processing<\/strong> if the applicant states so on their application. There is no additional fee for this. However, IRCC\u2019s officers will need to determine if the reason specified makes the applicant eligible for this faster processing.[\